<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>United States forward Alex Morgan has joined Tottenham on a short-term deal.  </p>

<p>The club announced released a statement on their club website confirming the move and said that Morgan has joined the club for the upcoming 2020-21 season from Orlando Pride.</p>

<p>Morgan has scored 107 goals in 169 appearances for her country and was part of the World Cup wins of 2015 and 2019. </p>

<p>United States forward Alex Morgan has joined Tottenham on a short-term deal</p>

<p>She netted a header in the semi-finals against England at last year's tournament, memorably making a tea-drinking gesture as she celebrated. </p>

<p>Morgan - who gave birth to her daughter Charlie in May - has become another among a number of high-profile names to have moved to the Women's Super League since the end of the 2019-20 season.</p>

<p>That has included four other United States internationals, with Manchester City having signed Sam Mewis and Rose Lavelle and Manchester United earlier this week recruiting Tobin Heath and Christen Press.</p>

